race.description: Alan Rummery Bookmaker Shane Connolly Memorial Hcp (C1)
race.comment: SHYAMALAN (1) is on debut for the Kelley stable following a 1.8L defeat at Wodonga 47 days ago. The blinkers go back on today and he'll find this a touch easier than what he was going around in recently. The inside draw is a big tick and he can make a statement. SHOWTIME MAGGIE (7) comes through a solid race here last time out over 1300m and that form may have been franked earlier in the card. She should get every chance from the good draw and she still possesses good upside. Can figure in the finish again. COSMIC ATTRACTION (6) had trialled plainly coming in and her fresh run left plenty to the imagination when beaten as the favourite. Blinkers go on now and she should be better out to this trip. Can improve. OUR LITTLE STAR (3) is racing in good order and won't be far away once again. NEFRADITE (5) won't be far away on the quick turnaround.
